{
  "goal": "Nhiệm vụ: Implement a 'Decoupled Reactive Orchestrator' using TypeScript Type-level 'Inference-Driven State Machines'. Instead of forcing complex conditional types that lead to recursion depth errors (Singularity Failure), use 'Generic Constraint Mapping' via an externalized 'StateSchema<T>' interface. This architecture will employ a 'Micro-Task Dispatcher' pattern where state transitions are not calculated at runtime but enforced through Type-level 'Branded Types' (Opaque Handles). This ensures that CoreKernel can emit events that AgentLoop and Memory consume via 'Type-Safe Subscriptions', effectively decoupling the execution lifecycle from the reactive side-effects.\n\n[Dữ liệu Tự Phân Tích]:\n- Ưu điểm mong đợi: Eliminates recursion depth errors found in previous attempts; achieves true zero-cost abstractions through Branded Types; significantly reduces cognitive load for maintainers while maintaining absolute type safety; enables independent scaling of Core, Agent, and Memory modules.\n- Rủi ro NGHIÊM CẤM vi phạm: Requires developers to understand 'Branding' and 'Opaque Type' patterns; slightly more complex initial boilerplate for defining the StateSchema.",
  "targetFilePath": "src/core/CoreKernel.ts",
  "testCommand": "npx ts-node --strict src/core/CoreKernel.ts && npx ts-node --strict src/core/AgentLoop.ts",
  "workingDirectory": "E:\\Project\\LIVA\\openclaw-gateway"
}

