  "goal": "Nhiệm vụ: Implement an 'Opaque Transition Engine' using TypeScript 5.x Private Class Members and Branded Types to decouple state management from the main execution loop. Instead of a centralized event dispatcher that causes Context Overflow, use a decentralized 'TransitionSchema<T>' mapping where CoreKernel emits non-forgeable branded handles (e.g., `StateHandle<Active>`) that are only valid within specific memory segments. This transforms CoreKernel into a high-speed Micro-Task Orchestrator that manages state transitions via Opaque Handles, preventing the recursive conditional type depth issues seen in AgentLoop.\n\n[Dữ liệu Tự Phân Tích]:\n- Ưu điểm mong đợi: Eliminates 'Singularity Failure' by reducing type-dependency depth; prevents context overflow during large-scale state changes; provides absolute type-level security against forged state transitions using branded/opaque types; significantly improves compilation speed by avoiding complex recursive conditional types.\n- Rủi ro NGHIÊM CẤM vi phạm: Higher initial complexity in defining transition schemas; requires strict adherence to the branding pattern across the entire Core and Memory architecture; may require specialized IDE support for optimal developer experience with opaque handles.",
  "targetFilePath": "src/core/CoreKernel.ts",
  "testCommand": "npx tsc --noEmit",
